{
  "text": "The 2 isoforms HSD3B1 and HSD3B2 (3\u03b2-hydroxysteroid dehydrogenase/isomerase) share 93.5% identity at the amino acid sequence (see data in the online-only Data Supplement). [CITATION_1] Immunohistochemistry with specific monoclonal antibodies showed that HSD3B1 is expressed in ZG but not in ZF, whereas HSD3B2 is equally expressed in ZG and ZF and also in APA. In APA, HSD3B1 is expressed at low levels but correlates with the expression of CYP11B2. [CITATION_2] Hence, the isoform HSD3B1 could be a promising marker for APA, a hypothesis that deserves further specific investigation.",
  "correct_citation": {
